blocks.question:
Given these two CSS rules, what colour will a paragraph with class='highlight' render in?

p { color: steelblue; }
.highlight { color: goldenrod; }

exercise.starterCode:
/* Three competing rules — only .btn-primary should win */

#submit {
  background-color: crimson;
}

.btn-primary {
  background-color: seagreen; /* TODO: make this rule win */
}

button {
  background-color: steelblue;
  color: white;
  padding: 0.6rem 1.4rem;
  border: none;
  border-radius: 4px;
  cursor: pointer;
  font-size: 1rem;
}

exercise.solution:
/* Remove the higher-specificity ID rule so .btn-primary wins */

.btn-primary {
  background-color: seagreen;
}

button {
  background-color: steelblue;
  color: white;
  padding: 0.6rem 1.4rem;
  border: none;
  border-radius: 4px;
  cursor: pointer;
  font-size: 1rem;
}

/* Alternative: raise .btn-primary's specificity instead of deleting #submit */
/* button.btn-primary { background-color: seagreen; } */
